9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 61, L.D. 96, “An Act to Amend the
10 Motor Vehicles and Traffic Law Governing Mandatory Driver's License Suspension for
11 Refusing Testing for Drugs or a Combination of Drugs and Alcohol”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Amend the Motor Vehicle and Traffic Law Governing Administrative
14 Driver's License Suspensions for Refusing Testing for Alcohol, Drugs or a
15 Combination of Drugs and Alcohol'
16 Amend the bill by inserting before section 1 the following:
17 'Sec. 1. 29-A MRSA §2401, sub-§5, as amended by PL 1995, c. 368, Pt. AAA, §4,
18 is further amended to read:
19 5. Failure to submit to a test, fails to submit to a test or failed to submit to a test.
20 "Failure to submit to a test," "fails to submit to a test" or "failed to submit to a test" means
21 failure to comply with the a duty under this chapter to submit to and complete a chemical
22 test under section 2521 or 2525 or tests to determine any presence or level of alcohol, to
23 determine any presence or level of any drug or drug metabolite or to determine any
24 presence or level of any combination of alcohol, drugs or drug metabolites. "Failure to
25 submit to a test," "fails to submit to a test" or "failed to submit to a test" does not include
26 failure to submit to and complete any standardized field sobriety testing.
27 Sec. 2. 29-A MRSA §2521, sub-§5, as enacted by PL 1993, c. 683, Pt. A, §2 and
28 affected by Pt. B, §5, is amended to read:
29 5. Suspension for refusal. The Secretary of State shall immediately suspend the
30 license of a person who had a duty under this chapter to submit to and complete a test or
31 tests to determine any presence or level of alcohol, to determine any presence or level of
32 any drug or drug metabolite or to determine any presence or level of any combination of
33 alcohol, drugs or drug metabolites and who fails to submit to and complete a the test or
34 tests.'
